<div id='communityQuestionsWithAnswers'>
<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/791124-does-anyone-out-there-feel-like-writing-a">Does anyone out there feel like writing a story inspired by a string quartet by Leos Janacek (there should be accents over the s, the a, and the c)? I ask out of sheer devilment because: 
Janacek wrote The Kreutzer Sonata inspired by Tolstoy&#39;s The Kreutzer Sonata which was named after Beethoven&#39;s Kreutzer Sonata, which was named after a man who, I seem to recall, never played it. 
This amuses me.</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_791124'><a id="like_count_community_question_791124" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/791124?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">6 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F141077.The_Kreutzer_Sonata">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/791124-does-anyone-out-there-feel-like-writing-a">5 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/791124-does-anyone-out-there-feel-like-writing-a">See all 2 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

