<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/3875148-galicius"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1621625959i/3875148._UY100_CR3,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/3875148-galicius">Galicius</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Part of the answer to your question: Beethoven only dedicated it to one Kreutzer a famous violinist of his day. The connection in the Tolstoy story is<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Part of the answer to your question: Beethoven only dedicated it to one Kreutzer a famous violinist of his day. The connection in the Tolstoy story is to the music teacher in the story. I highly recommend a reading in librivox. It's read in a very thick Brooklyn(?) accent that is amusing. I don't know the piece by Leoš Janáček but will listen to it.<br /><a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
