        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3231327430" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4893475256500181490">The same age-old story of suspected adultery and communal hypocrisy, that wouldn&apos;t certainly have sounded authentic at all hadn&apos;t it been the time when it was written; practically remined me of Chekov&apos;s Lady with The Little Dog midways. However, this is &apos;the&apos; Tolstoy&apos;s writing, and hence just as elucidated and grandiloquent as could have been expected.</span>
  <span id="freeText4893475256500181490" style="display:none">The same age-old story of suspected adultery and communal hypocrisy, that wouldn't certainly have sounded authentic at all hadn't it been the time when it was written; practically remined me of Chekov's Lady with The Little Dog midways. However, this is 'the' Tolstoy's writing, and hence just as elucidated and grandiloquent as could have been expected.</span>
